A three-year-old boy  died after a bookshelf collapsed on him on  at a creche in Bedfordview on Tuesday. Gauteng education MEC Matome Chiloane said he was  disheartened by the death of the child  at his school in Bedfordview. “We wish to convey our condolences to the family, friends and the school community,” Chiloane said. The MEC is expected to visit the creche on Wednesday to understand the circumstances that led to the unfortunate incident. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month. READ MORE